  RFC9759 [label="RFC9759
Unified Time Scaling for Temporal
Coordination Frameworks
2025", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="Estimating time requirements for tasks, both critical and mundane, remains a challenge in engineering, business, and everyday communication.  Existing models fail due to inherent unpredictability and inconsistencies in human estimation.  This document introduces the Two-Week Principle (TWP), a novel, universally adaptable time scale that seeks to standardize all temporal references to a singular, uniform duration.  TWP ensures clarity, predictability, and synchronization across all sectors that rely on time-based scheduling.", style=filled, fillcolor=green, fontsize=18, penwidth=3, fontweight=bold]; 

